<p>Global spatial autocorrelation was applied to analyze the distribution of FMD cases where all provinces were considered as a whole. Global Moran’s 
 <italic>I</italic> statistic was calculated to evaluate the degree of clustering. In this study, Moran’s 
 <italic>I</italic> measured the spatial autocorrelation of province locations and the incidence rate of FMD and was calculated as follows (
 <xref rid="ref-7" ref-type="bibr">Cliff &amp; Ord, 1973</xref>): 
